Russia, Ukraine, Turkey and the United Nations all signed separate agreements ending the standoff threatening global food security. UN Secretary-General Antonio Guterres said the deal is a "beacon of hope, a beacon of possibility, a beacon of relief in a world that needs it more than ever" as tens of millions of tons of grain are currently trapped in Ukraine. The US said it will hold Russia accountable for implementing the United Nations-led deal. It is the first agreement reached between the warring nations since Russia invaded Ukraine last year. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...